Name: Cafe Mamouche
Review Text: Customer service was good. The environment is cosy. In regards to food, the appetizer was good, main course was above average. The dessert was average. We had Moroccan tea at the end which was a good way to end the evening, and the taste of it was good (although if you've been to Morocco, the tea there is better of course).

Name: Cafe Mamouche

Review Text: Friendly welcome, and a very nice restaurant inside. The menu is not too extensive, which is good - and they had 2 specials of the day. A fantastic grilled halloumi, and I had an equally good couscous mechoui. Saved in my favourites! (I didn't mention the open kitchen)

Review Text: Amazing authentic Marrocan flavors, a connection with comfort home cooking food . The service is excellent and great choice of wines. The place is charming and perfect for a cozy evening around candle lights.

Name: Cafe Mamouche
Review Text: Great food, with multiple interesting choices on the menu. The service was excellent and quick as well. The outdoor seating area is a bit too small, however it's really enjoyable in the summer, and you can always sit inside if more space is needed.

Name: Cafe Mamouche
Review Text: It was an amazing experience with Moroccan food at Mamouche restaurant. High level of hospitality and very fast service. The taste of the food is very close to the original. The price is acceptable and worth it. The Moroccan wine  was very delicious. Definitely recommend it.
